fonts-hack (3.002-1) experimental; urgency=medium

  [ Paride Legovini ]
  * New upstream version.
  * Hack is now MIT/Expat licensed with no Reserved Font Name.
  * The fonts in this package are now built from their UFO sources.
  * Font variants now consolidated in a single fonts-hack package.
  * The OTF and EOT variants have been removed (discontinued upstream).
  * Bump Standards-Version to 4.1.3.
  * Bump debhelper compat to 11.

  [ Fabian Greffrath ]
  * Add Breaks and Replaces relations against the formerly provided
    fonts-hack-otf, fonts-hack-ttf and fonts-hack-web packages.

 -- Paride Legovini <pl@ninthfloor.org>  Wed, 14 Feb 2018 18:42:57 +0100

fonts-hack (2.020-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Install WOFF2 fonts, thanks Boyuan Yang (Closes: #863009).
  * Move web fonts to usr/share/fonts-hack, out of fontconfig's reach.
  * Remove debian/README.Debian, doesn't apply anymore.
  * Add CSS files found in build/webfonts/css/ as examples.
  * Simplify fixing font file permissions in debian/rules.
  * Fix vcs-field-uses-insecure-uri lintian warnings.
  * Update package description for fonts-hack-web.
  * Bump Standards-Version to 4.1.1.
  * Bump debhelper compat to 10.

